    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-03T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-03T21:00:00-05:00" n="45"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.50/90: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-03T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 3, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1172. Your 1605, October 1, 4 p.m.<note n="49" xml:id="d45fn49">Not
                        printed.</note> It would appear that at least certain of the Ministers
                    accompanying President Ríos entertain the belief that this Government is
                    prepared to bargain economic assistance to Chile for rupture of relations by
                    Chile. Any such belief is totally in error. Our position in the premises is set
                    forth clearly in the Department’s 649, June 6, 6 p.m. The only development since
                        <pb facs="0050" n="36" xml:id="pg_36"/> that time which at all bears on the
                    question was the statement that President Roosevelt made to Ambassador Michels
                    to the effect that this Government would provide Chile, in the case it severed
                    diplomatic relations with the Axis, (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) with certain
                    additional armament in order to place Chile in a better position to repel attack
                    from Axis quarters and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) with economic assistance in
                    the unlikely event of large-scale unemployment caused by the attack and shutdown
                    of Chilean mines by the Axis.</p>
                <p>It is believed desirable that there be no misunderstanding as to the attitude of
                    this Government by the President and the members of his party.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
